## Part 5: Transparency and Integrity

### The Clarity Request

**Me:**
> "In the process book I want to be very clear that I used Claude ai to brainstorm, answer questions, compile information, create the html file, and whatever else Claude ai did. My portion included the ideation, asking for the help, developing the tool into a framework that could work in many settings, etc. I have the ideas, just not the technical expertise. Also this type of back and forth is perfect for my AuDHD."

---

**ðŸ“¦ INTERPRETATION BOX - ACADEMIC INTEGRITY & SELF-AWARENESS:**

This statement demonstrated:

**Transparency:** Proactive honesty about AI collaboration (not asked, volunteered)
**Attribution:** Clear delineation of contributions (mine vs. Claude's)
**Self-awareness:** Understanding my strengths (ideas) and gaps (technical execution)
**Accommodation recognition:** Explicit acknowledgment that this process works for my neurodivergence

**What I claimed credit for:**
- Ideation and creative vision
- Problem identification
- Framework development and scalability thinking
- Asking the right questions and providing direction

**What I attributed to Claude:**
- Brainstorming partner (responsive to my ideas)
- Answering technical questions
- Information compilation
- HTML/CSS/JavaScript code writing

**The AuDHD connection:** Explicitly naming that "this type of back and forth is perfect for my AuDHD" showed:
- Understanding of my own needs
- Recognition that different working styles are valid
- Pride in finding accommodation that works
- Advocacy for neurodivergent-friendly processes

**This makes the project STRONGER, not weaker:** Shows self-knowledge, strategic tool use, and modern collaboration skills.

