**Code Implementation:**
- Wrote all HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
- Built interactive features (checkboxes, expand/collapse, search)
- Implemented data persistence (localStorage, export/import)
- Created modular, scalable architecture

**Documentation Creation:**
- Generated developer technical brief
- Produced process book templates
- Compiled this hybrid documentation

### The Collaboration Pattern

**Iterative Dialogue:**
1. I identify need or have idea
2. I articulate it conversationally (often imperfectly)
3. Claude validates feasibility and offers approaches
4. I make decisions based on my priorities
5. Claude implements to my specifications
6. I test, validate, and provide feedback
7. Repeat

**This pattern shows:**
- I drive direction and make all strategic decisions
- Claude provides technical execution and education
- Neither of us could have created this alone
- Collaboration leverages both parties' strengths

### Why This Works for AuDHD

**Executive Function Support:**
- Task initiation through conversation (no elaborate planning needed)
- Working memory support (Claude remembers context)
- Organization help (structures my scattered ideas)
- Sustained attention (can work in short bursts)

**Communication Style:**
- Iterative refinement (think out loud, adjust as I go)
- No judgment (safe space for "basic" questions)
- Immediate feedback (quick validation without waiting)
- Written record (don't have to rely on memory)

**Cognitive Strengths:**
- Pattern recognition (saw scalability potential)
- Systems thinking (designed modular architecture)
- Creative problem-solving (envisioned novel solution)
- Hyperfocus when engaged (detailed feature specifications)

